<h1 id="work-up-an-idea-from-within">Work up an idea from within</h1>
<p><em>If you have any questions about this action, ask us in Discord, we will answer there and add to an FAQ here.</em></p>
<h1 id="method">Method</h1>
<ol>
<li>Ask yourself the  <em>Core Personality Questions</em>  and  <em>Domain Knowledge Questions</em>  shown below.</li>
<li>Write down your answers below.</li>
<li>Try to uncover any startup ideas from your answers using methods outlined in  <a href="https://nugget.one/academy/stage/2/step/2">Step 2 - Learn how to be open when considering ideas</a>: think about the business domain, the market, the value chain, the “little snowball,” and think optimistically.</li>
</ol>
<p><em>It may be useful to ask your partner to help you answer these questions. Sometimes other people can help see things about us that we haven’t noticed.</em></p>
<h4 id="core-personality-questions">Core Personality Questions</h4>
<ul>
<li>What do people always ask your advice about?</li>
<li>What do you always talk about, so much so that your friends’ eyes glaze over?</li>
<li>In work, what has made you the most satisfied of all the things you’ve ever done?</li>
<li>In life, what has made you the most satisfied of all the things you’ve ever done?</li>
<li>If you could only ever achieve one great work in your professional life, what would it be?</li>
<li>What do you already do that you have never considered turning into a side project?</li>
<li>What is your favorite thing to teach?</li>
<li>What are your hobbies or special interests?</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="domain-knowledge-questions">Domain Knowledge Questions</h4>
<ul>
<li>What do you specifically do in your day job?</li>
<li>What do your colleagues regularly ask for your help with?</li>
<li>What technologies do you know inside out?</li>
<li>What tools do you know inside out?</li>
<li>What did you build for yourself that makes your life 10x easier?</li>
<li>What is your favorite subject to learn about?</li>
</ul>

